                            <comment id="12794466" author="rding" created="Thu, 24 Dec 2009 18:07:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In this case, a workaroud is to disable the multi-query optimization (use command line option -M).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12833204" author="rding" created="Fri, 12 Feb 2010 22:31:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The cause of this bug is that, because the output of orderby statement is consumed by both store (to &apos;full&apos;) and limit statements, the limit operation ends up in a subsequent MR job. Since data cross MR job boundary isn&apos;t order-preserving, the script produces the wrong TopN results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proposed solution is to replace the limit operator with an orderby-with-limit operator, i.e. the orderby operation runs twice. This ensures the correctness of the TopN results.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
